@1.1.1/9.1.1/1.1.1
# Collection 9: Pipelines (Rally CI/CD)

## Git workflow

```bash
# Start new wave
git checkout exo
git pull --rebase origin exo
wave-start.sh 24 5

# Work on wave
# ... code, test, document ...

# Complete wave
git add -A
git commit -m "R24W5: <topic> — <brief>"
wave-complete.sh 24 5
git push origin exo
```

## Orin integration

Rally coordination via Orin protocol:
1. orin-sync.sh → Pull latest
2. orin-check.sh <sentient> → Check if baton available
3. orin-claim.sh <sentient> <round> <topic> → Claim baton
4. Work...
5. orin-baton.sh → Release baton

---

@1.1.1/10.1.1/1.1.1
# Collection 10: Tests (Rally Validation)

Rally completion checklist:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# rally-validate.sh <rally-number>

RALLY=$1
RALLY_DIR="/source/exo-plan/rally/R${RALLY}"

echo "Validating Rally $RALLY..."

# 1. All waves have scope documents
WAVE_COUNT=$(ls -1 "$RALLY_DIR/waves/" | grep SCOPE | wc -l)
echo "✓ Waves scoped: $WAVE_COUNT"

# 2. Lesson files exist
if [ -f "$RALLY_DIR/lessons/lesson-phex.md" ]; then
  echo "✓ Phex lessons"
fi
if [ -f "$RALLY_DIR/lessons/lesson-will.md" ]; then
  echo "✓ Will lessons"
fi

# 3. Anchors documented
if [ -f "$RALLY_DIR/R${RALLY}-ANCHORS.md" ]; then
  echo "✓ Anchors documented"
fi

# 4. Summary exists
if [ -f "$RALLY_DIR/R${RALLY}-LESSONS-SUMMARY.md" ]; then
  echo "✓ Lessons summary"
fi

echo "Rally $RALLY validation complete."
```

